title: Boyd Senter - Solos And Senterpedes (1927-28) 24/96 vinyl
description:
BOYD SENTER - VOLUME ONE 1927-1928 SOLOS AND SENTERPEDES

24/96 MONO vinyl rip

SIDE A:

1. Down-Hearted Blues
2. The Boss Of The Stomps
3. The Grind-Out
4. I Ain't Got Nobody (And Nobody Cares For Me)
5. 'Tain't Clean
6. Eniale Blues
7. Just So-So
8. Prickly Heat -B

SIDE B:

1. I Wish I Could Shimmy Like My Sister Kate
2. Mobile Blues
3. Prickly Heat -D
4. No More
5. Original Stack O'Lee Blues
6. Original Chinese Blues
7. Somebody's Wrong

Side A, 1-8 & Side B, 3-4:
Boyd Senter - clarinet, alto sax
Jack Russell - piano
Eddie Lang - guitar
Recorded between June 9, 1927 & May 2, 1928

Side B, 1-2 & 5-7:
Boyd Senter - clarinet, trumpet
Mickey Bloom - trumpet
Tommy Dorsey - trombone (except on "Original Stack O'Lee Blues")
Charlie Butterfield - trombone (on "Original Stack O'Lee Blues" only)
Jimmy Dorsey - alto sax
Jack Russell - piano
Eddie Lang - guitar
Vic Berton drums (on "Original Chinese Blues" only)
Recorded between March 23 & May 8, 1928

1986 Harlequin Records HQ 2044
